This image is created using the extra features I have added to my ray tracer. The gear objects in the center are created
using the Constructive Solid Geometry system I created, by unioning 3 flattened & rotated cubes, and then subtracting a 
sphere from the center. I also used the instancing and node system to reuse the CSG gear object, also allowing me to make
modifications to the gear that are reflected in every instance of it. There is also a Depth of Field effect, focused on 
the gears, but is out of focus around the edges of the image. And lastly, I used a small area light I created to do the 
backlighting of the image to just soften the shadows casted in the front of the image a bit.